A RADICAL RIME

Oh, what can we do for the Boers ?

Now our troops they have slaughtered by scores, We admit that their treason Has excellent reason3

So England their mercy implores.

Independence we'll give them, of course, Since they threaten to take it by force ; For there's nothing so wrong As oppressing the strong; ’Tis a sin that brings endless remorse.
